data.text:

Our #1 goal is to ensure every student attends, and graduates from, at least a four-year college.

I felt less intelligent at my last school because all we did was art projects. I like learning about all the revolutionaties that helped free Mexico on the way to liberty.

How I found my friends? I moved to the classroom, and they welcomed me. I was always pretending, now I can just be myself.

When I was in the other school, I was so behind in my reading. I went up from a 1st grade level two years ago, to a 4th grade reading level.

Before I came to Wallace, I was a student who got fairly bad grades. I needed to get my grades up if I wanted to keep playing the sport I played. So my mom brought me to Wallace and now I'm getting As and Bs.

I want keep my grades up so I can get the job I want when I'm older. I want to be a veterinarian.

Altruismo house forces me to get outside of my comfort zone and become friends with people I wouldn't have talked to beforeâ€”and they're a really good person, and I should have talked to them before.

The community is really nice, you make a lot of friends here; there is really no drama. They're really understanding here and I feel at home and comfortable.
